metadata.name: lightscapes//linescapes//darkscapes #101
metadata.description:
A landscape made of monochromatic rows arranged by color to create an illusion of depth.

Each token comes with some fixed constraints, some constantly changing elements, and 3 possible styles.

The lightscape mode creates the most natural view, while the darkscape mode reveals the skeleton of the image. The linescape mode blends the two and looks a bit more like an illustration.

CONTROLS:
- click/tap on the image to regenerate and cycle through the different styles
- press 's' to download a png at the current resolution

Hope you like it,
Cino

metadata.name: Mur #325
metadata.description:
Mur is a series of computational drawings of stacked and falling bricks. The bricks are placed in different configurations of walls, towers, stacks and paths, and are then exposed to gravity. 

The graphics are coded with p5.js and the rigid body simulations with ammo.js. In live mode, press 's' to save a screenshot and 'e' to save a high resolution image. Press 't' to toggle textures. 

Each scene is drawn twice, first brick by brick as they fall or stay in place, then the scene as a whole. Mur is optimized for Chrome, uses WebGL and may not work in all browsers.

metadata.name: Grud #41
metadata.description:
Grud, a speedrun on 31st May 2022. 

The cousin of the BoodMoards, exploring some other shapes, colours and fun ideas. 

Made with p5js. 
23 colour palettes
10 background colours 
11 tile styles 

Big thanks to all collectors and shoutout to the Circolors frens for the support <3 

10% of mint proceeds going to the processing foundation 
42% of royalties to minters. 

Click the image or press 's' or 'S' in live mode to save a 2160 × 2700 png

metadata.name: Elemental walks #46
metadata.description:
"Elemental walks" is an exploration of the interaction and perception of two different systems. The generated double grid pattern transforms into a crowd of random walkers that move in a random but constrained way, forming a dynamic pattern. You can change the colour, pause, reset, slow down or speed up your walkers.

"r" to reset position or release the walkers
"p" to toggle pause/play
"-" to slow down
"+" for faster movement
's' save png
'j' save jpg

Click the canvas and the colour composition changes.

metadata.name: Shapes on a Plane #408
metadata.description:
“Shapes on a Plane” explores imaginary structures and worlds through simple shapes. It’s intended for small-scale print.

As a kid I was obsessed with Lego, Duplo, wooden building blocks... anything I could make something with.

I’d spend hours building things, imagining new worlds, new machines, new concepts, then i’d take them apart and create a whole new idea to explore.

To me, this piece to me is a reminder of that time - many days spent exploring ideas with those simple objects - no care for viability, for marketability, for audiences or business. Just pure fun.

Without this time in my life, I doubt I’d have found my passion for creating in the way I do today.

metadata.name: Celebration in Times of Measure #81
metadata.description:
Intentionally developed by placing constraints on the process.

Everything is generated by code written in P5js.

Press '1' for the default, textured version
Press '2' to add outlines and see the form structure

Press '3' to see a flat, untextured version
Press '4' to add outlines (flat version)

Press 'e' to end/skip the initial animation
Press 'r' to restart/replay the animation
Press 's' to save current image (in live view)

Created by Walter Anderson (@noxiarb)
